course_introduction:
This course will provide you with a state-of-the-art toolkit to innovate faster, more flexible, and more customer-driven. You will gain an in-depth understanding of creativity and design thinking, both in theory and practice, with emphasis on the latter. During the course you will learn design thinking principles to develop creative solutions for what customers really value. You will apply the learned skills in a real customer discovery project in collaboration with our corporate partner, design agency Liquid Interactive. The course will enhance your ability to increase value-added creativity at individual-, team- and organisation-level.

This course contains a strong Work-Integrated Learning component which will enhance your employability skills, thanks to the course's partnership with Liquid Interactive: https://www.liquidinteractive.com.au/

Course Changes in Response to Previous Student Feedback

This course has been modified based on prior feedback from students:

- Assessment pieces are now 3: 2 individual and 1 group-based. In the past, they were 4 (2 group-based and 2 individual);

- Requirements for Assessment 1 have been further clarified, offering sample structure of the document; moreover, Assessment 1 now required a specific piece of deliverable (user journey mapping contained in the report)

- Feedback by panel and teaching team on Assessment 2 and goals of the two types of feedback have been further clarified;

- More keynote presenters have been involved;

- Structure of workshops in preparation for Assessment 2 has been further clarified.

It is worth noting that the course maintains a strong Work-Integrated Learning component which is aimed at strengthening the students' employability skills. For reference on WIL at UQ, see: https://employability.uq.edu.au/work-integrated-learning
